f(x) = \ln x
\lim_{t\rightarrow 0}\frac{\ln(1+t)}{t}=1
\begin{align*} \frac{d}{dx}\ln(x) &= \lim_{h\rightarrow 0}\frac{\ln(x+h)-\ln(x)}{h}\\ &=\lim_{h\rightarrow 0}\frac{\ln(\frac{x+h}{x}{})}{h}\\ &=\lim_{h\rightarrow 0}\frac{\ln(1+\frac{h}{x}{})}{x\cdot\frac{h}{x}} \end{align*}
=\lim_{h\rightarrow 0}\frac{1}{x}=\frac{1}{x}
